INTRODUCTION TO 3 JOHN&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/p>
&lt;p align=center style='text-align:center'>Virgil Warren, PhD&lt;/p>
&lt;p style='text-align:justify'> I. Authorship&lt;/p>
&lt;p style='text-align:justify'>It is uncertain whether there is any evidence for
3 John ‘s being cited before the third century, if the Muratorian Canon speaks
only of two epistles of John. This lack of citation and mention is
understandable because of its brevity and the character of its contents. What
was said of “the Elder” in connection with 1 John applies here also.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>